    "headline": "Oil Prices Tumble on Iran Cease-Fire Deal. Why They Aren’t Falling More.",
    "summary": "U.S. oil prices tumbled more than 15% early Wednesday after the U.S. and Iran agreed to a two-week cease-fire and President Donald Trump said he would help alleviate ship traffic through the Strait of Hormuz.  Brent  crude futures  the international benchmark, fell 14% to $93.69 a barrel, while  West Texas Intermediate  futures tumbled 17% to $94.23 a barrel.  Prices jumped slightly as Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth confirmed in a press conference Wednesday that Iran would allow ships to go through the strait but that the U.S. military would be “hanging around” in the region.",
